Package: gwas2crispr
Type: Package
Title: GWAS-to-CRISPR Data Pipeline for High-Throughput SNP Target Extraction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Othman", "S. I. Mohammed", email = "admin@leopard.ly", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Provides a reproducible and fully automated pipeline to extract,
    process, and export significant GWAS SNPs for any human trait or disease (EFO identifier),
    ready for downstream CRISPR screening and design. Given any EFO trait and statistical
    threshold, the package fetches all significant SNPs, annotates their gene context,
    exports comprehensive metadata tables (CSV), BED files for genomic intersection,
    and FASTA files with user-defined flanking regions. Outputs are designed to integrate
    directly with downstream functional genomics tools (QTL, cCRE, on-/off-target analysis)
    and CRISPR guide design software. Optimized for batch, reproducible, and large-scale
    workflows in genetic editing research.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
